<p itemprop="description">A chief data officer provides strategic leadership for data across the organisation. They are responsible for maximising the value of data assets, establishing data governance, and driving data-led innovation to support organisational objectives.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Define and execute organisation-wide data strategy and vision</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Establish comprehensive data governance frameworks and policies</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead cultural transformation towards data-driven decision making</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Build and manage high-performing data teams across the organisation</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Drive innovation in data science, analytics, and emerging data technologies</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Ensure compliance with data protection regulations and ethical standards</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Influence executive leadership on data investment and strategic decisions</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Represent the organisation in external data leadership forums</li>
    </ul>
</section>

